cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the impact of user mobility on interference and outage correlation models in wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical calculations and modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Mathematical Analysis). Additionally, the paper discusses the correlation induced by the random waypoint mobility model, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to understand the impact of mobility on interference and outage, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
